guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"e2qjt","text":"*start with full tip boxes and use tips in coordination with your plate map, so you never get lost","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"bb08d","text":"*watch 1uL volumes in the pipet tip like a hawk - major source of variability","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"6v5ne","text":"*cap and gently vortex your *mixture per primer set* every 12 replicates or so, sometimes things separate","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"b3akk","text":"Dilute stock IDT primers to 100uM (see note in Guidelines).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7c2v6","text":"Use 'GogaLab-RTqPCR-Preparation' Excel spreadsheet to input your sample number and calculate reagent volumes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"50gaa","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"oeee","text":"Mix *total reagent volumes required* (see spreadsheet, green) for DI and PowerUP","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"91v1h","text":"Mix your forward and reverse primer pairs together, to a final dilution of 10uM forward and 10uM reverse. For example, add 10uL each of forward and reverse primers to 80uL PCR-quality DI for 100uL final volume.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"976pc","text":"Pipet 1uL diluted cDNA into respective qPCR well, aiming for the sidewall of each respective well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"553ba","text":"Add 19uL *mixture per primer set* into each respective well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8nat4","text":"Seal plate, and spin down 1000rpm for 1 minute. Use bacterial, not tissue culture, centrifuge.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"akr06","text":"Load plate into centrifuge and proceed using QuantStudio software suite.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
